DOCUMENT();        # This should be the first executable line in the problem.

loadMacros(
"PG.pl",
"PGbasicmacros.pl",
"PGchoicemacros.pl",
"PGanswermacros.pl",
"PGauxiliaryFunctions.pl"
);

TEXT(beginproblem());


$r=random(-6,6,1);
$s=random(-6,6,1);
$t=random(-6,6,1);
$u=random(-6,6,1);

$r1=$r+$s+$t+$u;
$r2=$r+2*$s+3*$t+4*$u;
$r3=$r-$s+2*$t-$u;
$r4=$r+2*$s-3*$t+2*$u;



TEXT(EV2(<<EOT)); 


The principle that you process the coefficient matrix only once is so
important that we need to practice some more.  This and the next two
problems all have the same coefficient matrix.  You want to process it
just once, unless you enjoy retracing your steps.


The solution of the linear system

\[
\begin{array}{rcrcrcrcl}
r &+& s &+& t &+& u &=& $r1 \\
r &+& 2s &+& 3t &+& 4u &=& $r2 \\
r &-& s &+& 2t &-& u &=& $r3 \\
r &+& 2s &-& 3t &+& 2u &=& $r4 \\

\end{array}
\]



$BR is 

\(r = \)  \{ ans_rule(10) \},
EOT
ANS(num_cmp($r));

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT)); 
\(s = \)  \{ ans_rule(10) \},
EOT
ANS(num_cmp($s));

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT)); 
\(t = \)  \{ ans_rule(10) \},
EOT
ANS(num_cmp($t));

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT)); 
\(u = \)  \{ ans_rule(10) \}.
EOT
ANS(num_cmp($u));






